      <h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>Q: Will I get notified every time someone submits the form?</h3>
      <p>Yes — you receive both an internal SMS and a task in GHL every time a new quote is submitted.</p>

      <h3>Q: What if a contact books before the 24-hour quote email goes out?</h3>
      <p>
        The Consultation Booked Goal fires immediately and stops the workflow. The contact will not receive
        the quote email or any further follow-ups — just the task assigned to you to prepare.
      </p>

      <h3>Q: Should I send any SMS or email manually?</h3>
      <p>
        No — all 10 automated messages are handled by the workflow. Your job is to respond to any
        <em>inbound</em> replies from contacts, and to complete your assigned tasks (initial call, appointment prep).
      </p>

      <h3>Q: What happens if a contact doesn't book after 11 days?</h3>
      <p>
        The workflow ends after the Day 7 Final Nudge Email. The contact remains in the pipeline at
        "Follow-Up Scheduled". You can manually reach out to cold leads periodically or re-enrol them
        in a reactivation campaign in the future.
      </p>

      <h3>Q: Can I manually add a tag to override the insurance check?</h3>
      <p>
        Please check with the admin before adding or removing any workflow-related tags
        (<code>insurance lead</code>, <code>federal lead</code>, <code>veteran lead</code>, <code>consultation booked</code>).
        Modifying these can affect which automated messages are sent.
      </p>

      <h3>Q: Where do I find the Custom Quote form responses?</h3>
      <p>
        Open the contact in GHL → scroll down to the <strong>Notes / Submissions</strong> section →
        click <strong>Form Submissions</strong> to view their Custom Quote answers.
      </p>

      <h3>Q: Who do I contact if something looks wrong in the workflow?</h3>
      <p>
        Contact the workflow admin (Rhett) via the internal team channel or by SMS to the internal team number.
      </p>
    </section>

